[
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The remaining calculation simply involves taking the first projections, which yields:",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "\n$$\n\\begin{array}{c}{(\\mathrm{pr}_1)_*(h_1-h_2)^l=\\sum_{a=0}^l(-1)^{l-a}\\binom{l}{a}h^a\\cdot(\\mathrm{pr}_1)_*\\mathrm{pr}_2^*h^{l-a}}\\\\{=(-1)^n\\binom{l}{l-n}h^{l-n}\\cdot d[X],\\qquad(l\\geq n)}\\end{array}\n$$\n",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "By substituting  $(15)$  into  $(14)$  we have :",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "\n$$\n\\begin{array}{c}{s(X,\\sigma_2(X))=\\sum_{l=n}^{2n}(-1)^{n+l}\\binom{l}{n}\\cdot dh^{l-n}-\\sum_{l=n}^{2n}2^ls_{l-n}(T_X)\\cap[X]}\\\\{=\\sum_{i=0}^{n}(-1)^i\\binom{i+n}{n}\\cdot dh^i-\\sum_{i=0}^{n}2^{i+n}s_a(T_X)\\cap[X].}\\end{array}\n$$\n",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "From equation  $(9)$  we obtain:",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "\n$$\n\\begin{array}{l}{X)\\times\\sigma_{2}(X))=s(T_{X})\\cap s(X,\\sigma_{2}(X))}\\\\{=\\sum_{i=0}^{n}\\sum_{a+b=i}\\{(-1)^{b}\\binom{b+n}{n}dh^{b}\\cdot s_{a}(T_{X})\\cap[X]-2^{b+n}s_{a}(T_{X})s_{b}(T_{X})\\}}\\end{array}\n$$\n",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "by omitting the pull back  $(\\Delta (X)\\to X)^{*}$  . Therefore, we obtain the main formula from equation  $(2)$  , which completes the proof.",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Corollary. The multiplicity of  $\\sigma_{2}(X)$  along  $X$  is  $d - 2^n$",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Proof. The multiplicity of  $\\sigma_{2}(X)$  along  $X$  is the coefficient of  $[X]$  in the class  $s(X,\\sigma_2(X))$  cf.  $\\boxed{8}$  Chapter 4.3])",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "5 Examples",
        "text_level": 1,
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "5.1 In the case of curves",
        "text_level": 1,
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Consider the case where  $C$  is a smooth projective curve. Let  $g$  be the genus of a curve  $C$  . The degree of each term of Segre class  $T_{C}$  is given by  $\\deg s_0(T_C) = d$  and  $\\deg s_1(T_C) = 2g - 2$  . By substituting those terms in the main formula we get :",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "\n$$\n\\deg \\sigma_3(C) = \\frac{1}{3!} (d^3 -9d^2 +26d + 24 - 6dg - 24g)\n$$\n",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "which can be found in [12 Proposition 1].",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "5.2 In the case of surfaces",
        "text_level": 1,
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Consider the case where  $S$  is a smooth projective surface. Let  $K$  be the canonical divisor of  $S$  , let  $d = h^2$  , let  $\\pi = h\\cdot K$  , let  $\\kappa = K^2$  , and let  $e = c_{2}$  be the topological Euler characteristic. The total Segre class of the tangent sheaf  $T_{S}$  of  $S$  has degree  $\\mathrm{0}$  , 1, and 2 terms, which are given by:",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "\n$$\ns_0(T_S) = [S],s_1(T_S) = K,s_2(T_S) = \\kappa -e.\n$$\n",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "By substituting those terms in the main formula we get :",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "\n$$\n\\deg \\sigma_3(S) = \\frac{1}{3!} (d^3 -30d^2 +224d - 3d(5\\pi +\\kappa -e) + 192\\pi +56\\kappa -40e)\n$$\n",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "page_idx": 0
    }
]